## Understanding

Issue #76 is the largest piece of the TypeScript CLI migration: porting the core automation loop from `scripts/loop.sh` into TypeScript. This means building the `processIssue()` pipeline (the 12-step orchestration for a single issue), session management, test running, learning extraction, and the `alpha-loop run` CLI command that ties it all together. It depends on three prior issues: #73 (CLI scaffold + config), #74 (utility subcommands), and #75 (engine core: agent, worktree, github, prompts, shell, logger) — all of which already exist on their respective branches.

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] `processIssue()` executes all 12 pipeline steps in order: update status, setup worktree, plan, implement, test+retry, verify+retry, review, create PR, extract learnings, update context, auto-merge, cleanup
- [ ] Failed implementation aborts and labels issue `failed`
- [ ] Test failures trigger retry loop up to `config.maxTestRetries`, invoking agent with fix prompt each time
- [ ] Verification retry loop mirrors test retry loop
- [ ] PR body includes review report, test results, and "What to Test" section
- [ ] `dryRun` mode logs all steps without executing side effects
- [ ] `createSession()` generates session with timestamp-based name (e.g. `session/20260330-143000`)
- [ ] `saveResult()` writes JSON result to `sessions/{name}/` directory
- [ ] `getPreviousResult()` returns the last result for prompt context injection
- [ ] `finalizeSession()` commits learnings to session branch and creates session PR
- [ ] `runTests()` executes configured test command, respects `skipTests`, handles preflight ignore
- [ ] `extractLearnings()` invokes agent with learn prompt, writes to `learnings/` only
- [ ] `getLearningContext()` returns formatted context from recent learnings
- [ ] `alpha-loop run` starts polling loop; `--once` exits after one cycle
- [ ] `--dry-run`, `--model`, `--skip-tests`, `--auto-merge` flags work
- [ ] Ctrl+C triggers cleanup (remove worktrees, finalize session, log summary)
- [ ] Startup banner shows all configuration before polling begins

